oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Major General Patrick Ronayne Cleburne
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Portrait of Major General Patrick Ronayne Cleburne (1828-1864) in uniform. Caption reads: "Original photograph taken in Mobile, Alabama, 1864. Only known picture of him taken during Civil War."
Served in the Provisional Army of the Confederate States of America. He was one of the five generals to be killed at the Battle of Franklin.
